  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;41 - Opening hours&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Any A3/A4 use in operation on the ground and first floor of the development hereby approved shall be carried out between the hours of 0800 to 0200 Monday to Sunday and on public holidays.&amp;nbsp;No visiting members of the\r\npublic, other than hotel guests, shall be admitted to the ground and first floor A3/A4 use after midnight (0000\r\nhours) on any day.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Any ancillary A3/A4 use in operation associated with the hotel hereby approved shall be carried out between the hours of 0600 to 0200 Monday to Saturday and 0600 to 0000 on Sundays and public holidays.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Any A1 use in operation hereby approved shall be carried out between the hours of 08:00 to 23:00 Monday to Sunday and public holidays.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;REASON: To ensure that the use operates in a satisfactory manner, and does not unduly disturb adjoining occupiers or prejudice local amenity generally.&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;35 - Energy Requirements&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Prior to the occupation of the relevant part of the development (part 1 – auditorium, kitchen levels 07-16) (part\r\n2 – remaining levels) the applicant is to submit the following information to the Local Planning Authority for Approval in writing:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;a) Air permeability test to confirm that the development has achieved the target set at 3 m3 /h/m2@50pa; and, &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;b) detailed specification confirming the glazing system has a U-value of 1.1 W/m2/K, and a maximum g-value of 0.35; and &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;c) a certification by an accredit PV installer confirming that an array with enough capacity to generate 14608 kWh per annum.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;REASON: To ensure that the proposed sustainability measures are implemented to a satisfactory standard as proposed.&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
